summary.text: 117 sewage discharge events were recorded across England, primarily involving Yorkshire Water, United Utilities, Severn Trent Water, Anglian Water, and Thames Water. The average discharge duration was 22.7 hours, with the longest single event lasting 20 days. These discharges occurred into numerous rivers and tributaries, including the Calder, Don, Derwent, and Humber catchments.
